                     <binding notAfter="1510" notBefore="1490">
                        <p>Stamped red sheepskin on boards, '+IHESVS MARIA' on a large stamp used twice on each side, with clasp fittings (clasp lost), about 1500 CE, London work, worm-eaten and worn.</p>
